  <h2>Where Did This Come From?</h2>
  <p>
    Omegon started as a fork of the <code>pi</code> TypeScript coding agent (omegon-pi),
    then rewrote the entire agent loop, TUI, provider layer, memory system, and orchestration
    engine in Rust. The TypeScript harness still exists as a compatibility shim but is being
    sunset — the Rust binary is the canonical runtime. See <a href="/docs/migration">Migration Guide</a>
    if you're coming from Claude Code, Codex, or another tool.
  </p>

